- Always write code in Roman English.
- Use TypeScript for all components.
- Style using Tailwind CSS.
- Keep components small and reusable (Atomic Design).
- Always validate inputs: Check for empty, negative, or invalid data types before saving.
- If a room type is not available, hide it completely (Dynamic Visibility).
- Maintain consistent padding, margins, and dark mode theme.
- Add descriptive comments to all custom business logic.
- For all forms, use inline field-level validation (red border + short helper text) and disable Save until errors are fixed.
- Centralize reusable validation/sanitization logic in shared utils and clamp numeric business inputs to non-negative values.
- Before applying changes, think: "Does this break the Transport or Visa modules?"
- Every time you modify a file, check if you have violated any rule in .cursorrules.
- If you identify a better coding pattern during this task, suggest adding it to .cursorrules before finalizing.